Mental Model
Cloud Run lives outside your VPC. Cloud SQL private IP lives inside your VPC.
To join them, you need three things:
(1) a VPC connector, (2) Service Networking peering, and (3) IAM on the runtime SA.
The runtime service account authenticates to Cloud SQL using IAM (cloudsql.client) through the Auth Proxy.
Invoker IAM only controls who can call the Cloud Run URL — not what the service can access.
